    • registerSpecies

      public boolean registerSpecies(String name, String scientificName, int isMigratory, int faunaOrFlora, int type)
      Description: Creates a new 'Species' object and saves it in the species array of the wetland. pre: The user entered all the species attributes correctly. pos: The stopFlag variable changes to true or stay in false.
      Parameters:
      name - String.
      scientificName - String.
      isMigratory - int It has to be a valid option (0 or 1).
      faunaOrFlora - int It has to be a valid option (1 or 2).
      type - int It has to be a valid option (1, 2, 3, 4 or 5).
      Returns:
      stopFlag boolean If it it's true, then the process was correct, if it's false, the process was incorrect.

    • calculateAmountOfMaintenancesInAYear

      public int calculateAmountOfMaintenancesInAYear(int search)
      Description: Calculate the total amount of maintenances in a year for each wetland. Calls the 'getType' and 'getYearEvent' methods of the 'Event' class. pre: The user entered correctly the year. pos: The variable changes to the amount of maintenances for a wetland, stays in 0 if it hasn't.
      Parameters:
      search - int It has to be a valid integer number (year).
      Returns:
      totalMaintenancesInYear int Has the amount of maintenances for a wetland in a year.

    • calculateTotalFauna

      public int calculateTotalFauna()
      Description: Calculate the total amount of fauna species in a wetland. Calls the 'getFaunaOrFlora' method of the 'Species' class. pre: The user chose the action of see the information of each wetland, see the wetland with the mosth fauna species or see in wich wetland is a species present. pos: The variable changes to the total amount of fauna species, it stays in 0 if the wetland hasn't.
      Returns:
      totalFauna int Has the total amount of fauna species in a wetland.
